 Entity

if ($entitygood == true) { ignorethispost }
else {

Alright. Someone who likes this episode please explain to me why you like it.
I just finished yelling 'LAAAAAAAAAAAAME' at the tv.

New gripes I've come up with after watching it on tv...not gonna bother rehashing my original problems with this ep.
1. That entity thing....why the hell would you tell your 'enemy' how you're vulnerable. I mean it just went and told them radio waves injure their world. Not very smart for a high tech being thing is it really.
2. That typing thing again. Except this time instead of the old 'hit three keys and out comes a sentence thing' I realised something else. The bit where the entity hits a few keys and then the voice says 'Then I am Major..' and jack cuts her off and goes 'no you're not'. In human to human dialogue you can cut people off like that...cause they'll stop talking when you start. But Jack cut off a machine...how come the machine stopped talking?
What...did the entity only type 'Then I am Major.' ? Like that makes sense?!?!
3. Anyone else notice the 'lightning plates' used in the Entity's nest? You can buy them at novelty stores....like the sort that sell lava lamps They use them in those borg bits in trek movies too..ahh how embarrassing.

On another note...it's quite humorous watching this ep again after not seeing it for a while.


}
